\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How old's Mary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I've no idea about Mary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 She'd be about fifty-four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Somewhere about that age. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Martha'd be a year or so younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye, be about - fifty - say about - approximately fifty. You cannot - cannot tell you correct you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Sixty - oh when I was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know how old he was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was sixty-two then. Sixty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 In 1924 wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He lived down the South, London way or something. But I couldn't tell you anything about his life down that area. Lived down the South.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was that before he got married, he came up here and got married up here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I expect so. He was one of the best, I can say that like. My father, one of the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was working on the ships, did he do that all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I can't really say but - he was pretty - about - approximately fifty years at sea, traveled all over the world like in different ships.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was his job on board ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But the reason - the reason - first mate I think they called at that time, of course he'd probably been an o
rdinary seaman to - you know, during his younger days but the reason he got this job on the tugs he had an accident, sprained his ankle you see and of course he was in the infirmary as they called it then and - he got put right you know then they gave him
 this job on the tugs you see, at home all the time, just going out to the piers, bring the boats in you see. They gave him that job 'til - 'til the accident that killed him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know whether he had any casual jobs or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, he ju
st - just - he was away at sea all the time like. 'Course he used to - there was a lot of time from when he going long distance journeys, he was - he was on the colliers you know, taking the coals from the pits from the harbour like down to London, Great 
Yarmouth and all these areas you know supplying, taking the coal down there on collier boats you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He probably had some long periods ashore though didn't he, did he ever do any jobs for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, when he - when he came from sea he'd 
only have sometimes twenty-four hours ashore while they got the boat loaded up. You see, then away down to South again, it kept backwards and forwards 'cos on the colliers like that they were only away about a week you see, they were back again and then w
hen they come back they loaded up with coal again and - away to different places there you see, down South. I don't know whether it was supplying the - for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 power}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  station them days, I don't know if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 there\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 be any or not. See? Or whether it was just supplying the householders with, you know, the coal and taking it to the depots or - you know, from the ship. to depots and supplying them the same as they do here you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 Did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't - not - I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Up 'til 1924 there wasn't so much of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No. I believe they did - there was a little time he was out of work and - it was a timber boat on the go then and used to come in with timber and he just used to get a casual big job t
hen you see. Just used to go down and they would perhaps set a score of men on to unload the timber boat. You see. Used to come in every now and again full of timber, that was - for general use and a lot for - pit props. Pits and that you see. Of course h
e used to do perhaps a day or a couple of days to unload it you see, it was all stacked up and taken away. I remember the name of the ship as well. The ship called the Oakwood. I remember that after all these years. Aye. She was only - little small boat.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I think she was about sixty-nine when she died, she died suddenly, I think she had a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know when she died - what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Be about - ten years after me father died wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 About 1934?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Somewhere about that region. Sixty-two - aye be about - should be close on sixty-nine to seventy I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did she come from, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well in her young days she belonged - I looked it up and like that she lived 
at Fenham. You see. It's - in a dispatch case that I have somewhere that tell where she lived in her childhood days she lived at the Fellen. Of course her mother lived at Blyth you see. Of course I expect - perhaps my mother's mother lived there you see a
nd she was there in her young days, a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 kiddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 like, and that's the time when probably - when the grandmother was - was my grandmother as I say was there you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So she lived in Felling and did she move from there to Seaham Harbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Must have done when they got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You think she probably met your father in Felling or after she moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Could say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know if she had any jobs before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't think so. No, I don't think she had any jobs. She just - well the house that's all. No, I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925  couldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about after she was married, did she ever do any jobs outside the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't think so 'cos she would have enough looking after the family 'cos there was the days then what they are different now you see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 
I mean your wash tubs in the - the wash stick when you did your washing and - and you lived all - two or three families all around in this big yard, you used to have to take their turns for a washday because it was the wash days t
hen with the little pinnies and one thing and another. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 The tap in the yard had to do for about six or eight of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So she didn't have any time for any full time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't suppose she would have any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Or any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
She had - already had - had a job looking after the household. 'Cos there was - there was about - there was three away at the pits and we used to go out at different times and all come in at different times you see, and the table was hardly cleared she'l
l have to set it out again you see. She had all - then we used to - when we came from the pit, after we finished our work, we used to have to bath in a tin bath in front of the fire those days, there's no baths then you see. You had your tin bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you tell me how many rooms there were in the first house you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well only about - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 Adelaide}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  Road, well it'd only be about two to three rooms.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Two to three bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, altogether. 'Cos, you know, there are - there were - the way t
hey lived them days are different now you see. There was no - no regulations about overcrowding or anything. I think it would be about - aye, would be no more than three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about Railway Street, how much bigger was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just about the same, three rooms. Two bedrooms and a kitchen they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And you used to eat in the kitchen and cook,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Uh-huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there anybody else living in the house, any relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No. Just the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother pay anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, she - 'cos when me dad was at home he used to do a lot of the cooking and - see me dad cooked, yes, and we had the - oh yes, we had - when the - when there was - they were all home that he used to have to - he used to
 peel as many spuds for us perhaps a stone of potatoes and they had a great }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 pan, a dixie as we called it, and used to make broth and everything. Big onion pudding in the - you know the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 dumplings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 in the clout them days. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What's a clout?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 A cloth. A clouty pudding, a clouty pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he ever do any cleaning in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh he used to - of course we used to have all brass candlesticks and brass - things on the wall and that, he used to often clean them. Those days they use
d to clean the house up about start on a Friday polish all the brasses and everything ready for the weekend, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he ever do the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, he do it - he did - his share, you know what I mean. Used to help a lot in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he keep the fires going?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes. 'Course those days with the big fires you could get two or three pails of cola on the fire. Used to have - fire was never out, was on day and night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he used to do that all the time that he was home,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh used to often - yes, he would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  after the fire and everything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about decorating in the house, wallpapering or painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, now I expect me father did help and me sisters you know, all - all did the sorting them out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Your father did some of that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he did, he was a proper handyman that way and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he do repairs and improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - perhaps if there was anything want doing it's - a landlord may have done it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was the washing always done at home or was it ever sent out to anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh she did it all at home as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother or your father make any of your clothes or mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well she used to mend to a certain a extent, 'cos w
e were - we were - you know, little rips them days running around you know. Of course we - a lot of time we used to run around in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 bare feet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  those days. The summer weather you know, used to run around in our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 bare feet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
. We were just - be more happier the
n, you know, running around - 'course we - we were just beside the beach you know, weren't very far away from it, we were never away from the beach, we were stripping off few a times a day and into - into the water. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You wouldn't wear out your shoes very quick would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your father ever do any shoe repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, he used to do the repairs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother or father make any clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I couldn't say that, I think she would - you know - buy most of
 them. 'Cos we used to - and little sailor suits were on the go you know, with a little wooden whistle and a lanyard round your neck. Used to be - those were the days of seeing these little sailor suits. 'Cos that was with Sunday wear you know, when going
 
out dressed on Sunday, went to church on a Sunday morning, used to get the sailor suits on. We had to go to church them days. But mind, I'll tell you when we came back from church we used to like to get more clothes on and away and running around you know
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were your clothes always new when they were bought or did your mother ever buy secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I couldn't say about that but I think mostly new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know where she bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just in the shops in the town like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know what kind of shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't know which shops. I should think most - perhaps in the stores for all I know. The Co-op. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there special times in the year when you used to get new clothes or was it just when they wore out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh, just when they wore out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your father ever dress or undress the children when they were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I expect he did his share of the house that way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember him doing it though? You can't remember him bathing any of the small children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well we just used to - perhaps wash ourselves when we were able to you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I was thinking of the children when they were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, probably he would do like as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember him reading to you or telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No. There's one - there is one time mind, I can remember when - sometimes he would - he would - I used to sing a little song to him and I used to get a ha'penny or a penny those days for singing a little song. And the 
song was in the shade of an old apple tree, a chorus. So that will tell you how old that song is.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he ever take you out on his own without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just used to - there were only one time he once took us to sea with him one time to t
he trip down to London on the boat. Aye. of course we were only away about four or five days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I was only - I was going to school at the time. I'd be about - perhaps about eleven or twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just you or your brothers as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, just me. Took us away for a - a sea journey. And the boat was owned at the time they called it the Lady Londonderry. Because that was - the - the Marquis of Londonderry, he was - owned all the pits round by Seaham and Dolton and round by }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 Sunderland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  way. Lord Londonderry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When your mother was out did your father ever have to look after you or was she always in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well she had to go out and do her shopping and all the likes of that 'cos me sisters - sisters was in the house y
ou know, used to - look after - the young ones then, what was young them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Your father was away mostly wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any jobs that you had to always do, like getting the coal in or going particular errands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 At home? Oh we used to run the messages, used to get the messages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there special ones that you used to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Oh we used to all do little bits, share. Aye, clean the shoes and - and wash dishes or done a little bit - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 might clean}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  up or anything like that. Get the coals in as you said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did you carry on doing jobs like this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, 'til we - you know - well we started work, we started in the pits when I was fourteen years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So when you started work when you were fourteen you stopped doing these jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - to a certain extent anyway, we didn't do a great lot 'cos - when you went to did your day's work at the pit, you come home, you get up about - go down the pit about at five o'clock in the morni
ng 'til about - two in the afternoon. Then when you come home you were tired and you - you got yourself bathed in front of the fire in a tub, a tin bath, and you went to bed. Used to get - well about six o'clock or something like that and - just get wash 
and tea and just go have a walk around you see. And perhaps go with the lads, our chums as we called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did the older children help the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I suppose they helped the small getting dressed and eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. They did all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 younger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  ones ever help the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, as I say they used - all joined in. Helped one another in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well we did like but - if we didn't go 
to bed we just sat in the house but we had to be in at a certain times at night, weren't allowed to go out at all hours of the night
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember any time when you were certain ages, like when you were eight years old what time did you have to be in at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well in the summer nights we could stay out like at - we used to have to play around the doors 'til - well perhaps nine o'clock or - and we use to come and sit in the house, it was time for bed 'cos we had to be up for school again and - and w
e got into this way where we polished our shoes at night. The - ready for the next morning to save a little bit time. 'Cs we weren't very far off the school where we lived in Railway Street and Adelaide Road, it was only five minutes off the school. And -
 the school was - is a Catholic school, St Mary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 Magdalene's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you were small did your mother used to put you to bed or was it somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just - put your nighties on and went to bed ourselves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Even when you were quite small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 How old would you say you were when you first put yourself to bed?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Now you're asking something. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How many people in your bedroom or in your bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh, perhaps two of us, sometimes must the one, but two of us. See o
ne got of bed when the other one come from work, he got in you see, there was like about - there was like three different shifts as we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 called}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  them, there's - went out at early hours of the morning. Five o'clock you used to go down the pit, then there was w
hat they call the back shift used to go down at - half past eleven and there was the night shift, you see, used to go down about six or seven o'clock at night. Come home in the early hours of the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Before you started work, there were four brothers, did you all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 share}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  one bed or did you have two beds in your bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 There's be two I should think. I can't remember that, it's a bit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did the rest of the family sleep, was it brothers in one room and sisters in the other, and what about your mother and father?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it was like the three rooms, it was just - all split up you see. Two beds in one room you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How often did you bath before you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well perhaps once or twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh every day. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the women in the family, did they used to bath every day as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, I don't suppose so. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How often did you change all your clothes before you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye, w
e - of course we - we were gong playing around, put clean clothes on we - the way we used to run about and that we - probably - had probably change the next day, well I should think two or three times a week we got our clothes clean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After you started work how often did you put clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well twice a week or sometimes once a week. 'Cos - no, unless we - we went out anywhere special or anything, we'd put clean change and - dress - dress ourselves you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did you used to eat your meals in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there any time when you ate in any other room or was it always in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, it was always in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did your mother cook? And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 In the - what would we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 say}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  - well, lot of the - in the scullery, was in the - scullery. She did cooking in the scullery. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 
And of course there was great big pans used to be on the big coal fire. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You know, you make a big - dish - dixie as they say, full of soup for the ten of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4459925  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 you, well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  you can just imagine the stuff that went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I'll bet it was tasty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. Yes, very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925  nourishing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she always cook on just an ordinary open coal fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye. Just - the big pans you know as they cal it, cook on an open fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What time did you used to have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh all times. There was no specified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 It depended who was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who was working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever sit down all together or when you had your breakfast who sat down with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 - when we were at home all sat together, you know. It was a big table you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you usually have to eat and drink at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh used to get all kinds, eggs and bacon and porridge and - various sort of things like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any different sort of breakfast on other days or was it always things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - just as you - what we could get them days, you know, 'cos we always got plenty but - there's plenty of good food them days, 'cos you needed it the way worked at the pits and one thing and another, you wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But it was usually these kind of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, egg and bacon and porridge was main breakfast them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you call the midday meal, did you call it dinner or lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well we - we used to call it dinner them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What time did you have your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well - anywhere between twelve and two o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who used to sit down to dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - when me dad was away we - we just used to all sis down and - of course me mother used to cook the stuff then when me dad was away.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you have for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh usual, potatoes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 cabbage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 , turnip and - you know - Yorkshire pudding as you called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you used to have meat often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Every day or just once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, sometimes we just had what we called a tea dinner. You know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 
Sausage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  or anything like that. Boiled eggs or something like that as they give you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have anything to drink with your dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Just were tea. Or perhaps - used to be a big jug of water on the table, anybody wanted to - a drink of water. Sometimes we used to have a teapot of tea put on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have anything sweet afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. Always a - rice pudding. Of
 course was baked - the rice pudding was put in a big dish, big earthenware - earthenware dish you see, '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 cos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 you can just imagine ten of you there again. Great big dish full of rice pudding. 'Cos my - use - eggs and milk there is half a dozen eggs, you know, put in, was the real stuff those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What other things did you have for the second part of your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well was only just mostly we had a good dinner and - then - perhaps a jam pudding or something like that. Roly poly as we call it, or sp
otted dog, currants you know. Just how she cut it up in slices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have anything different for your dinner on any special days like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, it was just more or less the same like. 'Course on the Sunday when you got the meat in we used 
to - you can imagine then the meat you used to get for - for ten of you in the family. Like - oh I don't know what would be - there was such a big joint. It would cost about - well those days you could get meat reasonable you know. She paid about ten bob 
for a joint of meat for a whole family. 'Course you - you wouldn't get a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925  lump}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  of meat then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the evening meal, what did you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, we just used to get the usual - jam and bread or perhaps as I said before, boiled eggs or bi
t of bacon or bit of sausage or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What time did you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well anything about five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you all sit down together to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well what was in house like if - we'd all sit down together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did the ones that were out working manage for their breakfast or dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well they just had it when they come in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any special tea on any special days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just the usual, you know, cake and - 'cos me mother used to do a lot of baking them days. She used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  a stone of bread about twice a week with - we called them stubby cakes but the real name is oven button cakes as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 They're like Newcastle flat cakes are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye. And we used to enjoy that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Anything special to drink at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just the tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was the dinner the main meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, at dinner time if we didn't have tea we used to get the bottle of lemonade or pop you know, orange drinks or anything like that. Ginger beer, that was 
on the go then. Used to get a bottle for - penny or tuppence. One of those three - three gill bottles, homemade. Used to go to a woman's father round the street that used to make it, there was ginger and there was what they called botanic beer. Herb beer 
y
ou see. But used to call it - and when we took the empty bottles back she used to give us a couple of sweets. That was make sure like that she got them back again. They used to charge penny or tuppence I think it was for the beer in them days for that, he
rb beer as they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You said your mother baked two stone of bread a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - on - on the average was - 'cos we were big eaters, we got well fed them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't - no, I don't think so. She used to just buy it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Any bottling of fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, she didn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, we used to buy them. 'Cos we were very fond of those days, pickles and beetroot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you used to buy them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 She used to buy them in the shops. She got most of our groceries at the Co-op. Them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she or your dad make any wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, me dad used to - it was - he used to make a medicine with - used
 to get - be sticks of Spanish them days. And - they used to call it licorice wine and used to make it in a bottle you see and we used - we used to get a drink every - certain while you see. And we thought it was great them days. Spanish - Spanish wine as
 he called it. It was just a stick of licorice soaked in the water and put sugar in or something. Bottled you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother or father grow any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. There was no gardens then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So they used to buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
 Well those days, what we call - get enough vegetables to make a big pan of broth for tuppence or threepence. You could get leeks, turnips - cabbage, used - yes, we used - what we used to - me mother used to get - tell me to go to so and so's grocers - fr
uit shop and get twopenno'rth of pot stuff. It used to comprise of that - perhaps a leek or - and a turnip and a few peas or barley or anything like that. You could get enough for to make a big pan of broth for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925  tuppence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  or threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother or father ever use any tinned vegetables or dried vegetables or fruit or was it all fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
I think it was just bought at the shops 'cos the shop - fruit and vegetable and shops was just round the corner you see on the main street. There was no gardens then much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you never bought anything in tins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did the family have any animals like chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, we just had a cat. Just a cat, they were the main animals them days. 'Cos we used to - used to get - have them - k
eep them for mice you know. The mice - 'cos they used - mice used to be in houses them days. Had a - used to keep a cat just for the reason, keeping them down you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you didn't have any animals for food, how many times a week did you eat }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7674431\charrsid4459925 meat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh it was two or three times a week we used to have dinners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever have tinned meat or was it always fresh meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 All fresh meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we got rabbits. Rabbit pie, we - we used to make rabbit pie for the Sunday as well
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did the rabbit come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well we just bought it in the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You didn't do any hunting or poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, no, no, you just bought them in the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember how often you had that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, perhaps, once a week or once a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Instead of ordinary meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 'Cos we - we were - used to like a roast - roast beef most of all them days.
