\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  because we know what we would get. When we got in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother used to say, go and hit him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, she didn't, no, no she wasn't like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Have you any idea what kind of a person your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye, she hoped we would all be good lads and - you know - and - nothing special that way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Anything that she thought was very important like being honest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well she believed - me mother believed in - well - me mother believed in me going to church on the Sunday. 'Cos
 she was very strict that way, we had to go to church on a Sunday morning. There was no getting out of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So that was one of the most important things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That was one of the most - that was - that was one of the important things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Anything else that was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
'Course we had - well, when we were youngsters we had to go to Sunday school as well on a Sunday afternoon, you see. But Sunday was the main day for church. No, she didn't do much work on a Sunday. Sunday was - Sunday wa
s what they called a day of rest after the dinner them days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did your parents thing about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh she were very strict against that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Both of them or just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh me dad - oh if we - you know, if we'd have said anything like that we would get spanked then. Get the strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - we didn't used to join in or anything like that 'cos if they were talking among theirselves one thing and another you
 see we just used to be - go out and play or that, you know, we were out of the house all the time practically when it was good weather but - you know, good weather we were off down to the sands, the beach. Docks and them places.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 On a day like this if there were two or three grown ups in the room and you were there as well would you feel like joining in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well if it was anything that I'd had anything to do with - the people asked for anything we used to just answer the question as best as we can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You told me that you got the st}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 ap quite often off your dad when you used to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 We - we didn't swear. We didn't swear, we didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 swear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 If you did anything wrong was it your dad who used to strap you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh used to get - oh me dad used to get - if me dad was home at the time we used to get the strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And your mother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. She would box our ears.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh time and time again. We were proper little rips them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Can you remember any special time when you did something that was very bad and you got punished for it, can you tell me about it?}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh aye, that was one thing, tearing my clothes. You know, perhaps if I had good clothes on we'd been playing about or anything, you 
know, knocking around where we shouldn't have done, well - tore our clothes we got wrong for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember how you felt when you had your ears boxed or the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - oh yes, we used to - like every - all the other kiddies, used to cry you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you feel that it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. 'Course she had a life with me you know, with all - we used to knock around you know. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think the ideas you got about how to behave you got from your mother or your father or from both of them.?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You wouldn't say that one was more important that the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well I wouldn't - no, they were both about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you had a birthday was it any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just used to get a - some sweets or - you know, somebody got a story book or anything like that to read or - some sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get presents from everybody in the family or just from your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, mostly me mother, you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have anything special to eat when it was a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, she made perhaps have a little birthday cake or - you know. And have a little bit cakes for tea you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you used to invite any people to eat tea with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Only - any - any of o
ur birthdays just perhaps some of the boys or lasses we used to play alongside with, used to bring them in. If it was any of me sisters birthdays they used to bring a playmate in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember doing anything special with your mother or father at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well it's Christmas Day we used to help with - you thought - you know, as we would say helped. You know. We used to polish the brasses just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 On Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, not Christmas Day. We used to go to church, we had to go to church on Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who went to church on Christmas all the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Everybody. Yes, everybody. And - of course - if me dad was home as I say he used to prepare the dinner. And - well it were Christmas dinner, Christmas pudding
 and all the rest of it like and that was that, then the rest of the days well was only quiet you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did anybody have any musical instruments in your house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did anyone used to sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. There - there was no - there was no wirelesses them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have anything like a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, no, nothing - nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you used to play any games with your parents, either indoor games or outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, story books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 ' books or adults books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, children's books and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Those were the only books were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well when I was a - a laddie I used to buy these twopenny - twopenny
 books, Sexton Blake and the like of those, you know, detective stories, I used to buy them and read them. Used to get them about a penny I think. I was very fond of reading like that. All about detective stores and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there a-y newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, there was the newspaper what they call the Sunderland Echo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How often did you get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I think we used to get it every night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 'Course the Sunday paper, News of the World - you know, likes of them, the People, the Sunday Express.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get all three every Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, we used to get one but them was the papers that was on the go then the same as the present day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Which one did you get though, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I think we - I think was the Sunday Express. Of course we didn't read them then. Just me dad and mum you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you had an evening paper every day and one Sunday paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. It only used to be a ha'penny I think for the evening paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 magazines}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, didn't used to buy - not unless any - me mother or any - got any given her or anything like that. Like the way the people today, likes of the Woman and them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember your mother 
and father reading, what did they used to read besides the papers? Did they both read the papers, your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. That was the - the main thing on the Sunday after dinner, they would just sit at ease there and read the paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they read anything else do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever read to your dad or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember there being a funeral in your family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember one as you got a bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, there was none then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You can't remember one at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were you ever taken out by your parents visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh used to - she used to take one on day trips down to Sunderland, down to Roker, we thought that was a great day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That was a day out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Not to visit anyone specially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, when we - to seaside you know. For all we lived at a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925  seaside}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  
place we used to go down to Sunderland to Roker. Of course that was a great day them days. We used to go down in a train, I think it used to cost her about - tenpence return in a train from Seaham to Sunderland. Used to go and - thought it was a great thi
ng going on the donkeys and that you know. Penny a ride on the donkeys. Thought it was great.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember going to see any people with your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, when I left school - when I left school when I was fourteen I got a week, me mu
m says, well, we'-l take you through to your Grandma's in Blyth. We'll have a week's holiday, we'll go and stay a week and I went down to Blyth to me Grandmother's stopped a week and I came back and then I - she took us up to see the colliery manager abou
t
 starting work at the pits. So - I got - an interview and I got started at the colliery and went on what they call the screens those days. Which like the coal coming out of the pit in the - in - we called them tubs, you would call them boats. They were ti
pped onto this screens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there divisions of interest between workers, between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, the craftsmen they got the bigger wage, a tradesman, there was a big distinction there between the labouring jobs and the craft
smen jobs. The labourers got a lot less that the - the craftsmen. A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 craftsman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 served his time at the - the trade of the craftsmen is to say tradesmen. Where a labourer just starts on a job and he's just told what to do, you know, seeping up or any other jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Do you think there were any other differences though, was it just the wages or were there any other differences between the craftsmen and the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, it's just - he was the top - the top man like, the craftsman compared to the labou
rer. The labourers used to have to - in the factory you see the craftsman in the factory, printers and the likes of that, you had to run about for them you see, go and get different parts for the jobs that they were putting up you see. You went to the sto
r
es with your - with your barrow or bogey and brought the stuff out of the stores for them to work on and assemble you see, to make a complete jobs. And mind you the fitters they were on bonus. Oh and the craftsmen, they were bonus going in the factories. 
But the labourers just paid an ordinary wage, so much a week, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was this the same in the mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well it's - it's different in the mines you see. A collier, well, if they had what they called a good cavill and they got plenty of coal out, 
so many hundredweight of coal a week and that it's like piecework. Of course there was hard seems and what they call soft seams. Coal was very hard that they couldn't hew it very much you see. 'Course it was all pick and shaft. You see. Hewing coal by han
d. And now it - and you paid - you got a percentage for - the piecework like the coals that - your weight turned up at the week, so many ton of coal a week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 This only went to the hewer did it, not to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No, there's - of cours
e there was putters. They used to get a percentage - of - how many score tubs of coal that - that - you know, bought out from the coal hewers every day, it was added up in so many score of tubs was put, used to get, after so many well you got a sort of - 
a
 sort of a bonus as well like, a sort of a piecework bonus you see. But if a miner had a hard cavill, what they called a hard place, hard coal, you couldn't get much - many tons out a week and he's only on what they call the medium wage. And that brought 
him six and elevenpence ha'penny per }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 day}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
, you see. For - of course it was really some of the bad place where - this medium wage, if they didn't make up the hewer didn't get enough coal out to make his wages up the foreman put so much towards that to make this medium wage }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 you see. Used to run - I know I've gone down the pit putting and coal hewing for five days a week getting up in the early hours of the morning for two pound two a week. That's for six shifts that. And a five day week you're still earning 
about thirty-five shilling or something like that. And then on the top of that every lad, they used to get tenpence a day rent allowance. So that was - say it was a five day week on the medium wage you just used to get about just over thirty shillings a w
eek. And with five - five shillings - five shillings rent allowance on the top that would have made it just over your thirty-five shilling a week for your five day and a six day week was two pound two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Not a lot in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think that your work has changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well it's - I many a time go back and think like however have I managed to keep going 'cos I've always been a hard worker. From the day I left school and went to the mines I've always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 been}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  a hard wo
rker, never known what a - a - light job was. In all the years. And I've wondered many a time wondered how I've managed to keep going and carry on. 'Cos I've worked long hours, down Vickers during the war work twelve hour }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 shifts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 , five - seven days a week during the war. 'Cos we used to go on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 fire watching}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  as well you see. Then we used to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 fire watching}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  school did you continue to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did the fact that you'd started work change your relationship with your mother or father or your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, it was just - just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the way you treated your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, we were all just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No difference at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But - might have had a little - once or two now and again like but nothing - to speak of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After you'd started work did you spend your Sundays any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, just used to go - well Sundays used to go down to the beach and, you know, different places round about for
 - the Dene and one thing an another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you used to go to Sunday school or church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, you used to go to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you carry on after you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Of course when we - but still I still went to church and when I went at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 
home}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  when I was in the pits and I still went to church on the Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you still go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I - of course after you left school well you didn't do any Sunday school or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Church, on the Sunday morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, there was just - just when the elections was on we used to go around with the boards you know, vote Liberal or vote Tory or anything. I used to go around with the boards, boards on the shoulder like a sandwich man. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Used to think it was great them days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just - just kid like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What were your political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Now well I - well them days I mean to say we didn't know much about it like that way. We k
now about it or anything because we were too young you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Up to the time when you were about eighteen, nineteen, twenty, what did you think about politics then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, I mean to say, politics then as - it's really different to what it is now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But did you support any party in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, it - we just - just vote used the vote for what we think would do the best, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well I was in the Army then. In the Army then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you'd be home probably some of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. Yes. Eighteen - nineteen - twenty-one. When I came out the Army the second time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 In 1919 you'd be twenty-two wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You hadn't voted before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody, such as your employer at the mine, or anyone in the Army, to voted for a certain party?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, no, I just - when we - when we voted you just vote for who would do the best.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You didn't feel you had to vote for someone to keep your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No. No, no. No, no. None of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever belong to a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever do any work for any apart from carrying these banners round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you spend your spare time after you started work, evenings and weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we just used to go to pictures. Pictures and sometimes we used to go down to Sunderland, that was only six miles away
, go to the swimming baths down there, for all we had these a five minutes from home, less than five minutes from home, we still used to go down to - to Sunderland to go to the swimming baths there, in a crowd you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How often did you go to the Sunderland swimming baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh sometimes every - you know, once a fortnight or sometimes - sometimes - every week or - 'cos there was - used to get the ram then. Used to walk to Ryhook and then used to get a tram to Sumderland for about a ha'penny or a p
enny you see. Used to go away of a morning and come back at - at night time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go out in the evenings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, we just used to walk round - Seaham you know, just round the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 sea}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  front and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just with pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Young men or girls as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Men. No, just the men. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 
Of course it was a favourite walk, there used to be the crowds getting - walking around sea front, backwards and forwards you know, it was the only way to put the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4459925  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 them days you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 In fact, there was no - there were - I don't think there was any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Sunday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 pictures or anything like then. I can remember in me young days used to go to a church hall and pay a penny and see a magic lantern slides and we thought that was great. It was Sunday
 night. Of course it was sort of a church - gathering you see. Used to put this - show on - films - slides and thought it was good them days. Pay a penny to see it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well occasionally - getting other
 new friends and all, you know, just the same - perhaps you would - maybe one would be away somewhere, go away or - that - but there was one - one mate of mine who kept together for years. But he - he went away as well you see, removed to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So when you made new friends was it usually people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 who\rquote d}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  moved into the area or would it be people you met who'd lived there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well people who'd lived there all the time. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember how you met new people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was it when you were walking up and down the seafront?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Just - just casual, get to know them by chance and that like you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever take your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 May have done like for a cup of tea or anything but - as far as I know, 'cos as I sa
y well the table - the table was always set like for who was coming in at different times when we were working you see, there was four of us at the mines you see, coming in at all different times. There were four of us in the wars. The four, the three bro
thers and me were in - were in the war, the first world war. And that's I said before, I lost one brother twenty-one years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 You}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  said you had one special friends, this lad you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 knew}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was he the same age as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - roughly about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he work with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, but we went to school together. We were playmates from school. The schooldays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Up until - when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 'Til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When was that, a long time ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh very long time ago. Years ago. Years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any other special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, I just - some of the lads that worked at the pits you know 'cos might be - you're walking round and round, it wasn't a very big place and you come down to the - - to the harbour
 for the shopping part you know and it - it's a habit of pitmen you know, they stand at the - used to stand at the corner end of the street. You know, and have a bit chat to one another and - the one - one thing of the old days and - or what you did at th
e
 pits and one thing - they didn't leave the work behind then, it was always - they were always talking pit working if they were standing at the corner of the street taking about pits just the same. The same in the pubs, got pit workers in there, just the 
same as - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any girlfriends up to the age of about twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No. 1919. Just before 1919 was when I met - the girlfriend now that I've got. Aye. Fifty one years ago. Fifty-one years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you see her very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well she was in the Army with us. Aye, she came over in the - she was in the Army and I was over in Ireland at the time, transferred over there so - and she came over in the married quarters. She was in there for so long then we - when we came back fro
m }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Ireland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  - she was sent to one place and we were sent to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother and father know your friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, they knew all - all my friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they expect to be told where you were going when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - we had to be in for certain times of a night like. Aye. Yes, yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, but we'd come in you know late on of a night, perhaps eleven o'clock or ten o'clock or something - different times, all depends. Of course i
f we were on the early shift - getting up at four o'clock in the morning to go to - to pits we used to like to go to bed a bit soon. You see 'cos when we came home - off the early shift, used to go to bed of the afternoon, perhaps get a couple of hours or
 something like that then get - get up at teatime then go out. Perhaps go to the pictures or just have the usual walk round you see, then come back home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you weren't told you had to be in by certain time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well not as I remember to a cer
tain extent we - we weren't what you'd call tied to be in at a certain time. Just came in - of course we didn't stop out more than about between ten and eleven, if we were at - any of me mate's house. Then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 come}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  in then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How old were you when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Be about - twenty-one I think. About twenty-one the missus is nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long had you know her when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh about - well roughly say twelve months, as near as I can guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember how you met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Wel
l it was - in the - we were in the parks, we used to get in the Regents - I think it was the Regents Park then, used to go around there and listen to band that used to be playing. And just as usual got into conversation. And of course we got to know one a
nother and went out together, then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 She belongs to Newcastle. She used to live down the - down by - off Stannock Street way, down that area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you save up any money before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, we did sort of save with what we could like. But were - what money you had them days. You didn't have very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your parents help you when you first got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, when we married, our wedding present there were - I think was a - a few pou
nds of - something about five pound or more. Of course that was a lot of money then. That was a lot of money them days then. See, five pound was a lot of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long were you engaged before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - two or three month.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you tell me a little about the wedding, where were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh we were married at St Mary's cathedral. And of course those days was a just a - a cab and a horse that took me down to the church and back you see. You know the old cabbie and the ho
rse. There was no big posh cars to - you know - not that I knew of then. And of course you had a do - you know, you couldn't afford the money them days to have a flash wedding as the saying is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have just the one coach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, just the one. Because I was in uniform at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So did you walk down there and your wife go in the coach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, she - I went first then he comeback pick the wife up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Then you came away together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How many guests did you have at the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh there was - there was just my mother on my side like and - see, there was all her uncles and aunts as went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So just two of you and about a hundred and fifty of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, there wouldn't be that many, no, there was
 - no, there wasn't a great lot like. Just had a little bit do in the room with a piano like. Bit sing-song and games and that as usual those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get many presents apart from this five pounds from your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't know that - of course the wife got presents of different things like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - sheets or - you know, anything that was usual in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go for a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No, I was in the Army at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 straight back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  on dury next day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye. I do - I had a leave you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But just a week I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you stay in Newcastle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just stayed in Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Where did you live after you got married? You were in the Army still weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Aye. But - I was in the Army but I used to come - had a sleeping out pass. I could sleep out but I had to be back in the barracks in the early morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have your own house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Stayed with her mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was that your home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That was our home for the time being. Of course, after being so long we got - we were in rooms, took rooms and stayed there for so long.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then she went to Ireland with you didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And she - I was shifted over to Ireland and - 
I was over there about six weeks and - and got word from the C.O. there was a - I think was a railway warrant to send for her to come over to join us, when we were there for so long like. And they brought us back from Ireland and they shifted her - the br
igade or the batteries like as we called them then back to England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Your wife was nineteen and you were twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Twenty-one, twenty-one I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your wife have a job when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, she wasn't working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Had she had any jobs before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 She had served time to be a dressmaker I think as far as I know. Well she did work like before I met here, she used to work in the town.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 As a dressmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just ordinary shop - a shop - shop assistant, serving you know. Big shop down in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she work after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, she didn't. She didn't work after we married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How do you think she felt about her work, working in the shop, did she ever tell you that she liked it or didn't like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - I don't know much about that but - during the hard time she did a little bit of sewing. Did a little bit of sewing to keep things going for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - it'd be after we came out of Army. Well if it wasn't for the missus well we would have been in a sorry p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 ight, I'll tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, we had - we had one child at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How many did you have altogether then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 We've just got the two. Two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When was the first boy born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 January 19 - I can't remember, January -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, one was born in - when we were in rooms and one was born at - the oldest one was born in where we were staying with her mother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes, we had the - the - the maternity hospital down - used to be in where the broadcasting place was, used to be there, of course - used - that's the help you got from them down there, the nurses. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Midwife}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  place or something. They came up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you help or did you get out of the way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh I - I was just in the - just in the next room, that's where we were staying with some people then. That's where - when me oldest boy was born. And - this was - this was her mother's, I was 
staying with her mothers. That's where we just all living there. In the kitchen part of the house you see. Her mother and her father and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How soon did your wife get up after the first child was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh be up at - eight or nine days or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she get up for the whole day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh perhaps for so long then - 'til she got her strength back again you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you manage when she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well her mother looked after it you see 'cos I was still in the Army then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Apart from her mother did anyone else help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well me mother was through the - she was - the home to run you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have a nurse at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, the nurse used to come each day you see for to - do the necessary, washing the baby, for so long you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did she come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just a few days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
How much did you have to do with your children when they were babies up to twelve months old, did you ever feed them or bath them or change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh I used to - I used to do me - certain - well she bathed the babies and that and - I used to look after them and take them out and one thing and other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you never bathed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, perhaps I did like and bath them and put the
m to bed or anything like that, the missus went out to the women's guild or anything like that I used to mind 'em while she went out and - 'course I went - if I went out well - we just have turns out now and again you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember ever changing their nappies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I didn't do much of that but she did most of that like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Will you tell me the date of your marriage again, it was 1919 wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Fifth of July 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember - what were your first boy's jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well he was in a warehouse, a drapery warehouse as message boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When was that, when did he start working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh that would be, when - 19 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 It'd be must before the war wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no - oh the - before this one, see we've had two wars
. The second one, the second one. When he was fourteen and take that - he would be fourteen from 19 - wasn't he message boy something else. He went - he was message for butchers. Then he left school, these are the times that you ought to have down, are yo
u taking that in, because they were really hard times, they were grueling times and - there were - bad. You got the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 dole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
, was two shilling a week - when he was at school. Each child two shilling a week. So he was due to leave school -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What year was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 1920 - he's the same age as the year. 1920. About then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So it'd be 1934 when he left school when he was fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He went to a warehouse, how long did he stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he was there about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was he doing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then he went on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was doing messages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was - yes, a sort of a message boy. And he left there and he went onto the railway and then the war started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did he do on the railway?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Porter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then he went in the Army and he was there all the war was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 All the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did he do when he came out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He went back to the railway. Aye he went back into that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did he stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - 'til - 19 - 'til 19 - aye, well about 1954 something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then he went lorry driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Lorry driving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did he stay on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he's there - he's still there now. Still there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about your second boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he - he went in - he went in the printing. Then he went to the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 February the third 1923.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So he'd be fourteen in 1937 so he'd start work just before the war and what was he doing in the printing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was in the printers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He worked in t
he printers. Well - he was just learning, bit of a message boy come, you know, learner. But then he went into the News Theatre. Oh aye, after that he went into the News Theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember how long, was it after the war started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, before the war. He wasn't in the printing all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was his job in the News Theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well helping in the - projectionist you know. Then he went in to the Navy. Aye, the Navy. He joined the Navy. The Fleet Air Arm. Joined the Fleet Air Arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was there until the end of the war was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 There the end of the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then what did he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He went back to the theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did he stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh about three year then he went onto railway. He went onto the railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 The same kind of job as his brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No. No. He - he was on manual work on the lines. But he's - sort of starting from the bottom and worked up, he's a sort of - he's supervisor or inspector or something like. On the signal, making signa
l boxes and supervising. To do with the signal and doing that. All this modernisation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He's in charge of all this is he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well he's not in charge but he's partly you know, he - does all the drawings and things - and he comes and shows the men whe
re his - there part is going to, and getting it all assembled and he tested it and try it and they do the work you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 He tells them what do, this, that and the other. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 It's all put - what's been and put on paper it's all done - in a way - workmanship you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What jobs have your brothers had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well they were - they were down the pits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they stay there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, 'til the wars - wars broke out and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After the war did Harry go back to the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He worked - he st
arted - when he left school the same as me, he was there the day to retire - retired. Aye, I was just going to say, with his Army service. He went into the Army during the war, he came back, went back to the pits after the first world war and he was there
 'til he was sixty-five. So he was there all those years excepting his Army service he was all them years from starting as a schoolboy, from school, to the day he retired.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was he doing most of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Coal hewing. Hewing coals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then Jim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Jim, well Jim was - Jim was at the mines as well. And he went in the army. Then he was over in India seven years I think. Came back. Then - he went back, got married and - lived in Plymouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What job did he do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't know 
what he did down Plymouth. Didn't know what job he did down there but - he went from there, Plymouth, to Liverpool and he's still in Liverpool to this present day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was his last job then in Liverpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was on the - the roads - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 asphalt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  - making the roads, you know, with this tar stuff and that, asphalt company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of job was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Making roads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was he a skilled driver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, you know, the manual work with the tar you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about Robert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well Robert, he was killed during the first war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did he do before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
He was - that's - Robert was the one that was in the Army before the war, you see. He was at the mines 'til he joined the Army before the war, peacetime soldier. And the war broke o
ut then he was - of course he had to go over to France when the war broke out, they were the first to go abroad you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of jobs has Cissie had?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just - she was always at home, helping in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He was - he was on the dole all the time. He could do anything but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 He must have jobs sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well I don't know what jobs he had like before her got married but - don't know much about his life as far as that is concerned. But - he didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about Martha?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Martha, well just at home just the same. Aye, fish and chip shop at night. The - never worked much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he's a miner. I don't know where he worked but he worked at down colliery, I think he w
as. Either a coal hewing or a stone man as they called it. I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What's a stone man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well it's - it's - no, it's the - well - it's - making either tubs going in for taking timbering up and one thing and another, general among workers as the saying is. Making places safe. Of course that's deputy as well you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he stay there until he retired or did he have any different jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he stayed - he's redundant now, he's redundant now but up to this last couple of years or three years he's - he's down colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And Edie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Edith. Edith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did she have any job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just the fish and chip shop. She worked the fish and chip shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well he was down the pits. He was a miner. Aye. He - we
ll was at Dalton he was as well or - or it was Dalton or same colliery he worked at.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did Mary have any jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Mary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
. Well her husband was a miner, he worked at Dalton, was it. I think it was Dalton colliery. But he - he had to give up work. He was on the sick for a long time and he had - never worked a-y more. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 He died a few years ago.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 (His wife) Have you had any jobs since you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh me, I've done everything. I've done every job. I've collected money for years. I did dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Any full time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh I never had full time, no, just part time. Collected on insurance and collected for clothing. And always sewed. You know, dressmaking. Always - always sewed, I've got handy fingers. Always sewed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you still do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
I could do if I wanted to, I could get hold of some now if I wanted. Well me eyes are going you see, I've got cataracts forming and they'll be - they're going any time. But I'm always busy, I never had time for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But this has been your main part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 Yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  I could - I could make a living at sewing but - I've had enough of it now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever go regularly to visit any neighbours or relatives who lived nearby, with your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well we used to j
ust go and - perhaps to the neighbours just round about the doors like just - talk about - well, one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you used to go with her when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Very seldom as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever go shopping with her or with your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I've gone shopping with me mother like at different times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your dad go shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't think so. All the family, you know, sisters used to go the messages or we went messages. Me mother went - got the messages.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Apart from that time when you went to London, did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he took us round and showed us round some of the places like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember any special places you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Tower Bridge and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That was when you were in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When we - when we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there any other time apart from that trip to London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, no, no. No, well he - he was no sooner home from one journey 'til they was away again you see. No, we just use
d to go out and play and - on the beach and round about you know, go different places. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Go over Dene - down what we called the Dene. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And the Eastertide we used to be a great day there, people all used to go down there and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 ice cream}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  parlours and fruit stalls used to be down there, the skipping ropes was all on the go and - various other things. It used to be a great day then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who did you go with then at Easter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we just used to all - just go down individually.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Not with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, no. Of course they would come down like or me sisters and brothers we were all down there, you know, sisters and brothers. Used to spend the day down there, used to take bottles of pop down there. You know, and a picnic- - sandwiches or anything like 
that and stay down there to night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever go on any trips with your mother and father or just your mother, like on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I daresay she's taken us here and there like but - can't remember the places like. We've gone down 
to Sunderland - often. To do her shopping down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever go away, apart from that one week with your grandmother at Blyth, did you ever go away for any other holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No, just that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did anybody in the family go for holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. There was - holidays was very few them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you spend Saturdays when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh it was just the same every day practically, just used to go on the beach and round by the docks and - or any other place, down the bu
rn as we called it. Playing around as usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You've all ready told me about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, Sunday regular day, church day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That's when you were your sailor suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Sailor suit with the lanyard round me neck and a wooden whistle and long trousers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you play any games on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well we did used to - a certain extent. We used to be - days when the marbles was on the go then. We used to play marbles. In the street 'cos there was no traffic them days, you could - you could lie down in the street them days and you'd be quite safe.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So your parents didn't think it was wrong to play on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no. Well, certain things mind but - marbles, used to play marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of games would they think it was wrong to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - it's a funny thing to say that but I can't remember that but - strictly cards or anything like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 couldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  play those you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, we couldn't play like but that was one thing there was strictly against, any sort of gambling or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But that was all the time, not just on Sundays, you couldn't play cards on Friday either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no. Of course we used to play snap cards just the same, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 little}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 e child's game, snap cards. But not the cards like what they have now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your parents think it was wrong to do any work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well they didn't think it was - there was very little 'cos we - the place was all cleaned up ready for the weekend, there was very little do on the Sunday. You s
ee, all the - as I said before, all the brasses and the steel fender was all polished up. Steel fenders those days. They were all polished. And everything was nice and spotless for the - for the Sunday. And we used to start somewhere about perhaps on the 
Friday, clean all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 brasses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 again, get the place - the house all cleaned again for the - the Sunday. As I say, it was a day of rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your parents used to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Me mam was at church every Sunday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 'Course me dad, he - like 'cos he was
 more at sea all the time, very seldom he had time to, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were they Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't know about me father. I expect he would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother go to church any other time besides Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, special occasions like - special church days. Always went to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go every week on Sundays and other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 We were made to go to church, we had no option, we were made to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 go}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  to church them days
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well other days. Special days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And you went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Mm-huh. Special days, what we called days of obligation. You see, them. We used to have to go them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, we used to go to - we used to go - but that was just what we used to go to what was called a school treat. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 We used to go to a place called the Dene - there were - further on than the Dene there was a place there was a big field and there was swings and all that in, just li
ke what you would call a park and we used to all go to this school and line up there and march out with the band, the school band used to play and all the banners and - little flags and that, we marched up to this park place and - we got tea there, bag of
 cakes and tea and games and all the rest of it, and of course that was a great day them days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
The nuns and the priests and all sisters and that used to come up with us. And keep us in step as much as they could as we're marching. And they used to dish the 
flags out to us before we set off. ad you come home in perhaps - about - six or seven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How often was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Once a year that was. What they call a school trip or a school treat. And that was a great day when we got the bag of cak
es and - pots of tea. Yes. That was great.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What other activities were there organised by the church, anything else, evenings or weekends, any clubs or things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well like there was the Catholic Institute like where - a sort like a boys club you could go there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well I didn't go very much like. 'Cos used to have - the band used to go and practice in the institute and it was just next door to the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there a choir at the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 At home did someone used to say grace before you started eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well as far as I remember we used to say grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Me dad like when we was all together like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you say prayers at night before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I used to say me prayers. I don't know about the others mind but - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who taught you to say your prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well learnt it at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Not at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, we learned that at - we learned that like what you call - we used to have a catechism of a
 morning you know. Used to have half an hour or catechism of a morning. And we said - we said prayers at dinnertime, grace at dinnertime and - I can't say for at night time. But we did used to say prayers part of - I don' know it was the dinner hour or wh
en we finished school at night. But we did say one part of prayers. And the - the religion of the morning, of the catechism from nine 'til half past of a morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any other prayers at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just - just the usual like. Nothing special. Well no - no special prayers like
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your family ever say prayers together at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I should think me mother would often say them to herself you know. Just - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your father take any interest in politics at all do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh that I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You don't know what his views were at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, no. 'Course there was Liberal - Liberal and Tory those days. There was no Labour. Oh yes. I know it was - I don't know what - the - what they voted for like but I do remember that, there was Liberal and Tory.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You don't remember either your mother or your father voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Sometimes some men thought they might get the sack if they voted different ways form their bosses, do you 
know if your dad had any pressures from his bosses to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 vote}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  the same way as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't think - I don't think he had any pressure like that. No. No. It's just the same voting as it is now. Secret poll you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You wouldn't know if he belonged to any political parties or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Just to the seamen's union - seamen's union belonged to that you know, missions to seamen. You know, joined that in case of shipwrecked well they get help and the likes of that as far as I know mind. Of cours
e he had to have a seaman's certificate you see - for to sail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When your parents weren't doing their work, what kind of things did they do to enjoy themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well - there was - I don't know - we used to have a gramophone you know, they're all playing the old records.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of records did they like best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - there were some of the ones, flat ones the same as they are now like but there was - time before that there was the old fashioned one with the - the roller ones. Yes. They were - they were the go then as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you have any of them in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Not - we had them in our house but I remember the time when they were on the go then. The - the Edison Bell records, that was - that was the type of record.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You don't remember any particular kind of music that you had in your house, the records?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, well - you know, different ones but I can't remember. But that was a great thing those days, having a gramophone. Playing the music. 'Cos no piano music and there only the - the silent pictures. They - they have a piano at the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother and father ago to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I expect they did do, I know I used to like the pictures, we used to go to the matinees on the Saturday, penny matin
ees see the pictures every Saturday afternoon for children, penny and tuppence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And you think your parents went in the evenings sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh probably went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 theatre,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  'cos there was the theatre there you see. I used to go and I used to like to - when I was going to school used to get in for about threepence or fourpence or something then. I used to like plays. Very fond of }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 plays}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 , going to see plays. And probably heard of a lot of - well some of them - the Fatal Wedding and Sinbad the Sailor
 and - well, Robinson Crusoe and all like that you know. Oh there was a lot of plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go to any of these with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well you just went on our own - we just went on our own like 'cos the theatre was only at the botto
m of the street. But we used to go to the matinees, I used to go as well at night time as I said - to the - see the plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any other things that your mother or father used to do, was your dad interested in any sports for e-ample or did your
 mother go to anything outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well she may have done but MI - I can't remember like any - any women's guilds or anything. I don't know. 'Course they used to get into neighbours houses and - and do a bit talking among themselves you know a
nd the likes of that, bit gossip is like going to a - a meeting or some description you see. That was those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But you can't remember your mother actually going out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Just excepting the pictures or theatre.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who did she go with when she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well, just went with her - her daughters. 'Cos me dad being away at sea you know. Just - he was away and perhaps come back through the week or come back at the weekend or he'd go away through the week. All the different ti
mes you know. As they loaded the ships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So your dad never got home from work each evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, he was away at sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How many full days a week was he away normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Going - going down to London and back if they set sail of a Monday 
they would be back perhaps about Thursday or Friday night. It all depends on what day set sail through the week you see, they may go away - they may go away on Friday and come back in the middle of the next week. It wasn't every weekend he was home or any
thing. Just the way the - the - outward journeys and back you see, the way they set sail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 It was quite irregular wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When he was home did he go to any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, he liked a - he liked a drink you know, the same
 as everybody else, he liked a glass of beer. And of course - the pubs you'd see you could go around to any of them within ten minutes. You know, they were all just bit in the - in the little area you see. Pub was just at the bottom of the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he go regular to the pub whenever he was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - he was at home he would perhaps go - even when he come back off his ship, you know, when they docked you see, if he was on his way home he'd - the pub was open he'd a call in and have a - perhaps
 a pint or - on his way home. But sometimes he would go out a night and have a - perhaps a couple with his pals or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did he ever take your mother out to a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, she didn't go to no pubs. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any clubs that he belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, there was no clubs then, what there is now you see. Just the pubs and the theatres, there was no clubs like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know if he was keen on any kind of sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well that's a question I don't know there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know if he ever went to horse racing or dog racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, no, he'd none of that. He might - he may have liked a little flutter on a horse or anything like that, but there were no dogs in them days I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know whether he did bet or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I can't say for sure mind. But just surmising this you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know if they belonged to any savings clubs, sick clubs or funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can't - I think they used to - they used to pay to a club like for the - for perh
aps trips or Christmas time you know, getting presents in for the Christmas. I think she used to - person used to call and - she used to give him so much each week. You see, just - just same as if you're putting it in the bank or something like that see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh very well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there anyone that you were closest too, that you got on best with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just about all alike I should think. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you went out to play did you play with your brothers or your sisters or friends in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just young lads. What we call our mates, you know. Perhaps some of the boys we went to school with, you know, together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So usually your mates rather than your brothers and sisters was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh we used to - we used to play together as well as I say, we used to play marbles, they were on the go them days you see, we used to play marbles and - spin - you know, used to have tops those days what you spin. That was a great game tho
se days. Whip and top. Used to play that in the streets, spin the top and keep rushing it - keep it spinning all the time, well that - that was a great favourite those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 All the kids in the street would play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. All the kids, that was a
 great game among the kiddies. Marbles and spin the tops and skipping ropes. Those were - those were the - the days, them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you always play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh used to play in the street 'cos you were safe there, there was no traffic. Ther
e was no cars - nor nothing to - like that. Quiet you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 If anybody wanted to find you they could just look in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. Didn't take much finding. Me mother wanted us she just used to come out and shout. We were there. Not unless we 
were away down on the - the beach. 'Cos we - used to tell her like where we were going and - you know, 'cos we were never away, we were always in swimming or something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Could you down there any time you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, on the beach yo
u could - there's any - we used to go - you could bathe any time there we used to go on the rocks when the tide was out and - get - catching craws. You know, the holes in the rocks and you have a hook thing and - used to put - feel the safe rock in for - 
o
h used to get many a crab. And you could get whelks and - of course limpets, they were them - it's like a sort of a thing that sticks fast on the rocks. I don't know whether you've heard of them. We used to often put them in the sea water and boil them an
d - light a fire on the sands. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother let you get dirty when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh - get dirt - we got dirty all right. Sometimes we would come in like crows. Playing about you know and - well you know what it is - round by the docks there's a beach and all that. We used to get all black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But she didn't mind too much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no. We were healthy and that was the main thing. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Could you play with anybody that you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, there was no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother ever say don't play with those or don't play with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, none of that. No. We just played normal like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you belong to any kind of clubs when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, there was no - no. We just went as I say, went to the pictures or
 the theatre. And - of course when I started work well, it all depends what shift I was on you see. That'd have to be soon shift. That was about only time 'cos you were in middle shift or the night shift as you say, well you couldn't you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you were at school did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - there's - I used to - used to like - I used to like painting. 'Course the - the schoolmaster - you - only one day a week we had painting lessons, on the Friday afternoon I think it was mostly, he'd giv
e us cigarette cards with flowers on and we used to have to paint it - paint the - the way - like the flower on the cigarette card. I used to get on well with that. 'Course I never bothered much with it since like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you paint at home or just at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just at school. For that was - that was your lessons you see, painting lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you do anything at home in the way of painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, never bothered, never bothered since I left school, I never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 
bothered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  any more of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 In the evenings or holidays did you do anything like modeling or stamp collecting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Birds nesting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well used to go around country lanes and that and - look at birds nests if we saw any. But - I never used to do - never used to do any 
damage to them or anything like that 'cos I do like to hear the birds singing and that. Especially the - even the blackbird or a skylark I used to - if out in the open the skylark I used to and listen to it there. That's one I thing I do like, to hear the
 birds sing, especially in the - out in the country in the open. Yes. I like to hear the birds sing, when the blackbirds singing on the housetops. We get them in the garden here anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You had some cats in the house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we used to - keep cat. We - we don't have cats like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes, cats were all the go those days, it's like the way people are having a lot of dogs now you see, but cats was the main - I should think were the main things just for keeping mi
ce and that down you know. 'Cos there's very old property then. 'Cos I mean to say they're - they're pulling - pulling Seaham Harbour down now and rebuilding the same as they're doing everywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you collect anything when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just used to save marbles up and one thing and another and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you do any gardening at all, you didn't have a garden did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No garden, no, no, no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about fishing or walking or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, me and one of me 
brothers, we used to go have a country walk through the night and just have - have our meal and go down to - to the place and fish through the night after we'd finished work, 'til about breakfast time and come home and get bathed, it's gone black. The bla
ck muck - coal muck on you. Just have a meal when we come in. About two or three o'clock in the morning. Then we were going out, took the fishing line and go out fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever do any fishing when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - little bi
t yes, we used to go fishing for crabs. As well as go on the rocks 'cos used - just used to put - as I say limpets or anything on a bit of loop on a string and just drop in the sea, well - the crabs come and they nip it with their nippers and we just used
 to pull them up. Oh aye, I've had a few nips with the crabs and they can nip as well with those claws. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Is it easy to catch crabs that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, you just - you just throw your - your line in to rest the sea bottom, you just used to pull it 
in now and gain to see if there way anything on it. You see, well you just throw it back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever cycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, we used to do that - well, cycling, we used to - have a bike and run around the place you know, down to Sunderland or any
where round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was this when you were still at school or after you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who did you usually go with when you went cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well - Sunderland and - round by Seaham colliery and - Easington and round there you know
, all around, just within a certain area, not too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go with a big group of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well any - any of the boys that had bicycles you know, just used to - just for a bit of a ride out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any sports that you were keen on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well - no, I didn't go in for any sports then but there were sports for them that wanted them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You said you went the theatres and cinemas and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I think that's one thing I told - pictures, I loved the pictures and I like to see a nice good picture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes. When I was at the pits. When I first went to the pits when I got about I think be - I said I think I said before about ten shillings a week for ten hour shifts, for five - five days. It was about ten bob a week, I got ninepence pocket money.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How much did you get when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just got paid Friday penny as they called it. Aye. But those - it was pay - pay day once a fortnight them days. 'Til later o
n when they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 altered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 it to once a week. 'Cos was grand when - pay day, the womenfolk all dressed up in all white aprons on and pinnies and house all cleaned up waiting of their husbands and that coming in with the pay. If he was a pitman. When the golden so
vereigns was on the go then and the half sovereigns. 'Course the - it didn't run to much like, if you got thirty shillings or two pound for a fortnight was good pay then. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you got this penny what did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh used to go and get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 ha'porth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  of sweets, you could get - you know, you get a lot of sweets for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 ha'penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 those days. Aye. You get a quarter of sweets for a ha'penny. Yes, four ounces of - four ounces a penny and two ounces a penny and all different kinds you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you usually spend it on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did anybody outside your house help your mother looking after the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 As far as I know - me mother did all the house - and the sisters, me sisters. I don't think she did need anybody. Ther
e was always the help in the home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So when your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well me sisters - sisters looked after us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your parents have any relations living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Lets see, I think there was a - there was a woman at Easington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That was the nearest was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was that one of your mother's relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
As far as I know like. Be one of me mother's. Probably - I think the one at Easington awas - me mother and her might have been sisters as far as I know like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember any particular friends that parents had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I don't - it's a - it's a job trying to remember that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think they had the same friends or did they each have their own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, they just - you know, went to - as 
I said, friend to each other's houses and - had a bit talking you know around about different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your dad go to the same houses when he was home as your mother did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, me dad just kept - you know, what time he had when he was home, 
well - as I say they - if he fancied a glass of beer he would go out with perhaps his pals, some of his mates that's on the same ship, go out and have a little drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So they probably had separate friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, separate way - that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your dad ever invite his friends into the house or did he only see them when he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he just saw them when he went out mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well she's had neighbours in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - two or three times a week. You know, come in some day with a bit gossip.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they have anything to eat or drink when they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well have a cup of tea or - you know, a cup of tea and a cake or anything like that. Whatever was - I don't t
hink there would be any - there was any drink on the go. She didn't have it in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you ever get friends calling in casually without being invited or did they wait 'til they were asked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no. Oh well, perhaps drop in like and just pass the time of the day and a little bit crack and away again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Would you say that most of the friends were neighbours as well, did they live nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, you see, there's two or three houses, there was a - a big yard you see and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  abou
t four or six houses in this big yard and there was a tap in the yard, you had to go outside for to get water and the toilets was outside. And - as I've mentioned before, you had your washdays, Mrs So and So was on Monday, Mrs So and So was on the Tuesday
, you see, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 unless}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 Mrs So and So wasn't going to wash that day. They - they would ask - were - one or the other would ask you see and you could go and wash. That's the way it was worked in. Of course - as I say, they used to have a boiler in the washhous
e, they don't - not like the way they have now with the boilers inside the house, was inside the wash house. And you just had to go and light the fire in the wash house, the - boiler fire. And everybody used that you see. There was no washers or anything 
like that. You can just imagine what our mothers went through in those days. Terrible amount of washing. In a big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So her friends sere nearly all neighbours were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh they were all round about you see, they - you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 church}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  people and all likes of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When your parents got together with their friends, did they ever meet each other in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well sometimes they did. Come into the house at evening - at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of things did they do, did they just sit and chat or have any music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes, yes, sit and talk and one thing and another and - you know - different things. Mrs So and So has been very ill and Mrs So and So's in hospital or anything like that you know and - the usual crack about one thing
 and another. The rest of the day in the week and one thing and another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You don't remember anybody coming in and playing some music or organising some games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, no. 'Cos there was no - no pianos and the music - just the - they used to put
 the gramophone on and - you know - there would be daft carry on among theirselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
A lot of people think you can divide people up into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 1918? I was in the Army then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Before 1914 then, just before you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, of course there was the boys scouts on the go if you wanted to join the Boy Scouts or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 People talk about working class people being down here and upper class people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, no, they weren't - no, no, we were just - we were just all one you see. No, it was - no there was - 'course as I say it was mostly mining place there you see. 'Course if you - you 
was to go out and stand the bottom of the street and - you know - or - and talk and the likes of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Which class or group would you say you belonged to yourself, you say they were all the same, can you give a name to the group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 There was - the
re was no groups as the saying is, if you met anybody outside you just talked to them or - there's another thing there on the - the Salvation Army, that was a great thing when they used to stand on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 treet corners I used to like to - if were mostly of a
 Saturday or Sunday night. That there was one place we used to assemble then, the way they do now, sing and play their instruments and that sort of thing, I used to - stand and listen to them, used to go their specially just to hear the - the band playing
 and the cornet players. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember being brought up to treat any kind of people differently than others, were you ever taught to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 touch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  your cap to some people or show respect in some way to special people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well, we were taught to respect people - you know - it didn't matter what they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 It didn't matter what job they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What job they did, we were always taught - to respect them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you were a boy was there anyone that you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember anyone who showed particular respect to your parents in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, not as I say - just the neighbours or perhaps - priest may call at her house or anything like that, parish priest. Say how you keeping, and all likes of that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 
'Cos it was always Father and - you know - always address him as Father.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who were considered the most important people in the town at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it's hard to say there, there's just - Lord Londonderry, he was a - as I said before, he 
was one owned all the pits round there. The mines, Seaham colliery and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Dalton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 and Mount Weymouth and - and - he owned that - he - owned a lot of the ships that used to take the coal away. "course he - I don't know - he died a lot of years ago I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did his family used to live anywhere near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I don't know where they lived exactly 'cos he used to live in Ireland. In Ireland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You never met him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, oh no. 'Course he used to come down sometimes, he used to be here like. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 'Cos there was a big - on the seafront there there's big offices, main offices where everything was controlled, you know, worked from there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
And what they call the - the Terrace. And it's still there at the present day as far as I know. Yes. Been there all them years. It's just on the cliff top at Seaham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Why do you think these people were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
'Cos they were - he were - he was a billionaire as the saying is. Coal and ships and railways there at Seaham, for the running the wagons of coal right from the pit right way down to the - to the stairs where they load the boats you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the shopkeepes, who did they spend their time with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Shopkeepers? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they spend their time with each other or did they mix with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh they just - you know - just spend their time on their own mostly 'cos - shopkeepers - you went in and did your shopping and then you - 'course you know you had a bit talking, one thing and another. 'Cos there's some shops there where we used to be
 going there for years, me mother. Yes, years and years we dealt with them. 'Course mostly - she was mostly for the stores. The Co-op. No, well that's what they call it, they didn't say Co-op then, it was the stores you see. Funny that isn't it. Aye. Aye,
 well I still call it the stores you know, I forget myself, say the stores instead of the Co-op. Aye, it's just the way that - you know. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the clergy, the Catholic priests and the Church of England people, who did they spend their time w
ith, do you think they kept to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes, we wouldn't mix - mostly kept to themselves. 'Cos there was the nuns there and they had the place - the place like a - the same as they have down the Cathedral there where - stay there you see, the nuns up there at this place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well, everybody nice to schoolteachers. There was mostly the schoolteachers of my days there. There was a few who came from Ireland. I can remember their names, some of them anyway. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they form a special group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well were all in the different classes you see. Yes, you had your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 exam}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  and you - if you passed your exams you moved up, the same as they do now in the different class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Would you say the teachers were as important as the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well they were them days 'cos they had a job you know. Had their job to do them days and - like we used to - if we didn't do what we were told then been - in the front of the class, used to get brought out and get the cane. Yes. Got to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you know any farmers near Seaham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Yes, there is a farmer there was - well for a lot of years, not there now though. Yes, I knew a farmer there. Used to go out there to the - to the house to the dairy part we used t
o get a can of fresh milk for a penny. Straight from the cow. Warm when you got it. A can - canful for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 farmer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  get on with the other people in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh he's - he was a well - well known man, very kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What sort of people would you say went to the Catholic church and those who went to Church of England and those who went to chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well was - there was all different religions there, people just went to their own church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any different kinds of people went to different churches would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 Well Catholics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  went to their own church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But were they different people in any way from the Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, they just they seemed ordinary people, shopkeepers and all - all - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you got shopkeepers who miners who were Catholics and shopkeepers and miners who were Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You got the whole lot in different }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 religions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  you see, the whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think that all the people had the same standard of living or where there some who lived better than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I daresay there might be some better than the others you know, 'cos they - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  and the likes of that well compare them to the miners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Take one family that was fairly well off like 
a trades family, tell me something about the things they used to do that showed they had a higher standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it didn't show like not to a certain extent, it just - maybe better classed dressed and the likes of that you see. As - as far 
as that's goes. More of a bit toffish, you know what I mean. Of course you know, the miners - you're always - most of them wore caps those days and mufflers and you know it wasn't the collar and the tie business those days to what it is now like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you could tell them by the way they were dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh you could tell a miner - a miner a mile away. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  always wear collars and ties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, you know, collar and tie and the likes of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there any other differences that you could see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, I think it's just - that was about the - the little variation there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8938769\charrsid4459925 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  felt that they were better than the miners?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it stands to reason they were - I should think - you know, they were the moneyed people. you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you hear anybody saying anything that would make you think they thought they were better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well to - to a certain extent I should think they would say that. We're better than you. But - that's about all it come to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were some families among the miners that everybody thought of as being a bit rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  of them a little bit rough like but - otherwise they were quite ordinary. If that was a crack you got - you got - 
you pulled - you got into the pubs. The Magnet then. It was all pit work all over again because leaving the pits started talking about pit work in the pubs, you know, that was the crack then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there families that were thought of as being rather respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, well I mean just to say that - the shopkeepers and - shopkeepers and - and - no, I think they were just like most - just as ordinary people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you hear any difference between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, if you - if y
ou were just an ordinary labourer they were better class than you 'cos the - the difference between an - an unskilled man and a skilled man, bound to because you - you've been educated, you've served your time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did this show itself in the way they lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well it did in some cases but not in others you see. But even up to the present day, well I'm a better man, a skilled man, a tradesman. That's what causing the strikes that's putting - the chaps - chaps that's doing tradesman's work and t
he tradesman - all doing this you see, it causes his work out and like of that. 'Course it didn't happen like that them days to what it is now. If you give one another black look they come out on strike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother and father think that shopkeepe
rs were a bit better class, did they think that labourers were not quite so respectable and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well I - I wouldn't say that because there was respectable labourers just the same as - as the better - as - as what you call - as what we could call better class. Yes, there were - they were just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, she was just an ordinary working woman, at home, house. No, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 
didn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  consider herself above anybody else. Just then ordinary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 housewife}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, for example, could a labourer become a craftsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I daresay if he wanted to like, if he wanted to, I don't know whether - go to a school or anythin
g like that - to learn trades and once thing an another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember anybody who did make this move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No. No. No. 'Course you - you see, you serve your apprenticeship. You see, you got - probably might have been the same then as did now. You 
see, but you're eighteen - well, years and years ago well boys used to go down the pit at twelve years of age. You'll have read about that 'cos that - that would be along before my time of day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh - I don't know about that either. I's - can't - aye. As I say, there was Lord Londonderry, he was a nice man, and his Lady Londonderry. They were very nice people, that's the only thing - kind of thing there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh yes. Policemen used to come round on their beats, just - yes, they just used to come round on the beat. 'Course one policeman - one policeman nowadays - them days could - could manage the - the
 likes of a small place like that. If you saw a policeman they used to run away. Aye. A policeman, he was a policeman them days. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you were a bit frightened of him were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, were dead scared of policemen them days. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Would your mother ever say when you were naughty, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh aye, fetch - tell a policeman or there's a bogeyman coming or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How do you think the policeman treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh very nice, the policeman, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yet you were frightened of him?;
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. 'Course those days as well it - policeman when any drunks were locked up then he used to just march them to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 police station}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 , you know, take their arm and take them, there was no - black marias or anyt
hing that I know of. I've seen them - policeman wheeling drunks in a barrow to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 police station}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
. Yes. Aye, I've seen that. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That'd be Saturday night I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it - you know - just how the - they spent their time you see and - 'course
 more the weekend you know a chap'd get, you know, one over the eight and - perhaps get himself into a spot of bother and - and couldn't - move himself you see because he just picked 'em up and just wheeled 'em in a barrow to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 police station}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 . Kept 'em in a cell or - kept 'em 'til they sobered up you see, perhaps might have got a summons and getting a big fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 The landlord did used to come I think but I can't remember the name of him now. They used to come - they used to come every week I think.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, just used to come and get the rent and - sometimes he'd sit and - you know - have a bit talk or anything like that
 or talk at the door about one thing and another but - if there's anything wanted done to the house or - take it down and probably get it done you see any repairs or anything. The same as they do now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you feel that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
They did, they had some hard times. Yes. Yes, when me dad was out of work well - a while there one time, we just struggled. Was - no, it was when the pit strikes was on them days, you see, you didn't get - 
you didn't get very much then. Had a struggle to make ends meet. And wonder many a time up to this present day, I many times think the times she must have went through. To feed us. It was a right job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Can you think of any differences to the family life when your father was ill or out of work, how did life change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well you - you know, missed out of the house and - when we lost me dad he was - he was missed out of the house and began to feel it you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I meant differences in the things you used to eat and your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh I see what you - we still got our meals, we still got our grub just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You can't remember any big differences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, life went on just the same like, as much as it was - could. Wasn't much change. Just
 when we started to leave home, you know, there was - there was the four of us in the Army. I lost one brother up on the Somme. He was only twenty-one years of age. That's the one that was in peacetime Army you know, before the war. I've been all round th
e
 place where he was - where he was killed. And - I had a brother in the Army and he was - he was out in India for six or seven years. And - then there was - there was me, Harry, Robert and James. There was four of us. There was the one that got killed at 
twenty-one years of age and had a - the oldest brother, I met him in France, come across him in France one time up at Ypres. Funny that isn't it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When your dad was out of work or when he was ill did you ever get any help from the guardians or the parish or any kind of charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well there was very little guardians them days, I think if you got any you got about half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you remember your family getting anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I can't remember that. I don't know whether me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  had - anything or not as far as that but it - it used to - it's like going for a court martial those days. You know, applying for relief or anything, it wasn't very much that you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well we didn't know much about i
t then days like not - we were too young to - you see. Bit - bit of grub and - but I don't know how the devil me mother managed it. Yes. We might have gone short a little bit but we've noticed - haven't noticed it. We had a good mother and everything, she
 looked after us that way and a good dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was there somebody in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I know a lot of people didn't like to go to the - to the guardians. They were people - they were people mostly I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
When there was somebody that did something that everybody hated was there any special way that the people had of showing that they didn't like this person, there was something called rough music, have you heard of that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Banging on kettles and make a noise outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Or like sending someone to Coventry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye, I know what you mean but I don't think there was much of that. The only rough music - wild music there is in the pubs of the weekend
 like the same as they have here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I was thinking of when somebody does something that's not very popular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well you know, when we were kids used to get up to all kinds of pranks you know, knocking on peoples doors and running away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That wasn't because you hated them was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. That - that because - no, just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 devilish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  tricks you know - little - quite innocently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I'm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 thinking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  of people who did something that everybody though oh that's very bad, we can't have anybody like that living here, and they tried to get rid of them, did that ever happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well there may - may have been like - noisy neighbours or anything like that. 'Cos you just had to put up with it. You see. You just had to put up with it, you couldn't do nothing about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or by a tutor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just by the teachers. But - but we learnt it just at the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I'd be five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we started - we went to school - we had to be in school for nine o'clock. Used to come out twelve. 'Cos we didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10168680\charrsid4459925 leave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  far away we used to come home for our dinner. Then we used to go again half past one 'til four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you started afternoon school at the same time as you started morning school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. We went from - nine o'clock in the morning. Then we got - we got the break off for dinner time, come home, got our dinner
, 'cos them that was at - for long journey well they just used to bring their lunch or whatever it was with them, sandwiches or anything like that. Or perhaps - got something outside you see. But - as I say we came home for our dinner every day, 'cos we w
e
re only in fact five minutes - five or ten minutes off the school you see. We could leave the house at five to one, be in the schoolyard by one o'clock when the bell rang. If we were lat - if we were late for school we used to get the strap. Get the cane 
for being late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you went even when you were five you went morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Afternoon. Oh yes. Then we used to get out about half past - I think the infants got out about half past three and - the older ones got out four o'clock. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Catholic school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was it boys and girls together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Boys and girls - no - well there were boys and girls but the boys were in one side and the girls at another. Sometimes it maybe - male or - all female or male you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you get to school, did you always walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. Well it was only as I say five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just used to go ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 On your own or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. Just - or perhaps - 
there were no - the - brothers used to go you see when we were all at the one school. Or any of the school boys that we know like meeting them on the way, just - there was no special anybody come calling on while you're going to school or anything like th
at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you think of school, did you like it or hate it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I liked to a certain extent but I many times wished like I was ready for leaving school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well the teachers were all right, 'course you 
got disciplined you know if you - being inattentive or - you know - at school and you got your sums wrong and we used to get the cane or - anything like that. Not knowing different answers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of things did the teachers think were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, got the usual history and geography and sums and all the rest of it you know. The usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they also put a great stress on good manners and tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, yes, we used to - used to pass remarks, different - diff
erent pupils you know, it - of course, we - I'm not boasting or anything like that but we had little, you know, little collars and the teacher would say, my that's a nice and - nice collar and - you know - this that and the other. Of course you would get 
the odd one like that come in sort of not too well dressed or anything like that you know and - they've even come to school in their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 bare feet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  some of them. You know, poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So the teachers were bothered about people being tidy and clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well, to a certain extent you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the way you talked, did they criticise the way you talked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, it - just carry on just the same you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Anything else that they thought was important, being punctual you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, you'd get the cane like, ask you why were you late, you know, get some excuses
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 If you did something the teacher didn't like did you always get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well you - perhaps get a little chalking up or you might get the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they punish the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 To a certain extent they did mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 They used to cane the girls did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, they got - all got treated a like practically.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What kind of things did you get caned for mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well you know, not p
aying attention to the - to the - you know - lectures out or anything like that. Put it down to inattention. Caning, you got cane. Or she may just tell you to - to pay more attention to your - to what she's talking about and that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were your parents interested in what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No. Well, you know, they would - they would like to know how we got on, of course you used to get exams every now and - you know - for passing into different classes you see. I said that a while back didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 They used to ask you what you did at school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well, it's just they knew you see what - what it was - what we got - 'cos we used to tell them, we'd say, we did this today and we did that, did something else tomorrow you see and that, we used to get the different subjects all different days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did your mother or father visit the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh they met the teachers, could meet them on the street or anything like that and just stop and talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did they ever go to the school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, only thing is if we was ever any off colour and we lost - we had a - we couldn't come to school perhaps - me mother gave us a note or any of the other ones if she couldn't get up herself, give a note to take to the teacher w
hy. Why Johnny was out, you see, Johnny wasn't well or Jimmy or anything you know, any of them in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did the other children in the school all come from the same kind of home as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well most of them, most of them. The most of - lot of them are miners children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 There weren't any kids that were very different as far as the home's concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, just about the same I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you notice that the teachers used to pick out any children and treat them in a different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well might have been - there might have been an odd favourite here and there like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you notice anything about the favourites?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well she would - of course - they call them monitors nowadays - she picks - give the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 pencils}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  out or give the books out or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Any particular kind of children who were monitors though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, well - I used to do it one time. Give - I used to give the things out. Mind I used to get me cane just the same, oh yes, I got kept 
it over the lockers. But I used to give the books and pencils and that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No, there was none of that, not to my knowledge anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were there any groups of children who used to go around together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well perhaps they did like as school pals, perhaps a few of them but there was no rough work or anything like that. You - you don't do it them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925  notice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  any children who were left out of things or always on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 'Co
urse I mean to say if you were rough in the schoolyard or anything like that and - perhaps one of the boys would tell so and so's hit us or anything like that. He'd be brought in front of the schoolmaster. The schoolmaster come out. Perhaps keep him in fo
r an hour - half an hour at night after the school's finished. Punishment you see. Quarter of an hour, anything like that you know, keep them in a bit later after the school's all gone out you see. That was your punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you notice any particularly lonely children in your school, any kids who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 didn\rquote t have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, not that I know of like I think they all mostly had - their people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go to another school after this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was the school called by the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 St Mary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 Magdalene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 . The same as the church. St Mary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 Magdalene's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Would you have stayed at school longer if you'd had the chance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I left when I was fourteen, I don
't - I don't think - I think you left when you were fourteen you don't get the chance then what you did here you see. Of course I daresay - me - I don't know but - may - them days, of course people would want to get their children, you know, get them to w
ork for - help the household you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 But if you could have stayed until you were fifteen or sixteen would you have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Aye, well, I don't think I would have done this. I was glad when I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you go to any night classes after you left school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. Just went - left school and - and - went back to the pits - went straight to the pits from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Have you got any regrets about your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 education}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 -n?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, I've - I'm pretty - you know - as I can't grumble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you think you benfitted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, well you know, things I've learnt and one thing and another. Of course - as they say as you get older you forget bits of things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you thought it was not so bad but you were glad you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 While you were at school did you have any part time jobs or any means of earning a bit of extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well I just used to go around with the papers of a morning. Used to - early on morning before school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you get the job in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well I just went and applied for it in the paper shop, a big paper shop, they used to print - a sort of little monthly magazine as well, we used to get paid so much for delivering those round the doors you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you hear from your friends that there was a job going there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, I just - just happened to hear like - a notice I think it was in the shop window, new paper boy wanted. And I used to go to the station of a morning with a little barrow an collect the b
undles of papers, bring them down and get - the amount I required you see and go deliver them before school on the morning 'cos we used start school at nine o'clock in the morning so I had to be up pretty early then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What hours did you work exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well it was - morning and - and - for the morning papers and night time for the evening papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 From about six o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - perhaps about an hour and a half or something like that - more than not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Was Saturdays the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we did - we did the Saturday nights papers just the same. And the morning papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
I can't remember that now. Probably - we may have done but I really can't remember that. I think we did and News of the World was still on the go and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 Dispatch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  and the other newspapers. Of course that was in me home town then you see but - don know what other papers was going. But I remember - well remember the News of the World and the Sunday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 Dispatch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  'cos I used to - yes, I used to deliver them. I can remember well now that's come in my mind you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Seven days a week then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Aye, seven days a week. We got three shillings a week mind for that. Delivering all - we had about - six - about sixty papers to deliver at night time and of course just a few in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you think about the wage, did you think it was a good wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well it was reasonable those days. Yes, it was - yes, it was - it was a lot of money like to the work. It always helped the house you see, the
 - 'cos I had a brother was with us as well, he used to deliver the papers as well so that was six bob a week coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you give any of it to your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh we give it - yes, we give it to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 All of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 All the money. Yes. She give us a little - perhaps two or three coppers you know for - to spend you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 She just put it in with the housekeeping did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, it all went in - just the same. 'Cos }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 these}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  - was a - was a family so we took some keeping mind. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you get on with the people that you worked with on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh very well. Yes. Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How about the boss, did he treat you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes. They had a small printing business inside the - the place you know, at the b
ack part of the shop, this small printing - used to print this - little monthly news magazine you know for about locally and adverts and one thing and another you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you like the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it w
as just a - was - a bit of a rush you know getting up and getting around of a morning to get finished for school time nine o'clock in the morning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did this job change the way you thought about school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, no, no, we just - it was just a little job that was all, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you do any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No. No part time jobs, just the papers. Newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did you get your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well is - is when I left school
? Well me mother took us up - went and saw the manager at the colliery, Seaham colliery, and - see about if we could start work. And - of course I got the job without any bother and - I had to start on the screens, what the screens - they coal it came out
 
of the pit on a conveyor belt, they called it the screens you see. And - that was picking all the stone out of the coal as it came along the conveyor belts into the wagons when they were going down to the docks to load the boats you see. And I started fou
r
teen years of age and I was on the screens as I said, I was on there nine weeks and we used to take your turn to go down the mines - pits. It came that I was saw - had to see the manager and I was told I was going - would be going down the pits. Well I wa
s - let's see now - fourteen - I would be there about - two to three year. 'Course the war started, the war broke out and I enlisted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you worked there for just those few years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, but after the war - the end - was over - or just before the war came on when I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When you first went down the pit after you'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 worked }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 on the screens, what did you do when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 went own}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well - well the names we had, we were just called - flapping. That was just coupling tubs on for the - it's the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 came out to the flat, you see, coupling the tubs up and then the drivers used to take them out to the landing where - the sets were up to about sixty tubs you see, they went out - were hauled out to the shot you see, went out down by to the sh
ot you see and come out in - a cage and, as I say, onto the screens and into the wagons and the wagons used to go from the colliery down to the docks. And the boats were loaded with the coal that came down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did you work on the flats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 We
ll it was - the way you start - you start from one right from the bottom you see, flatting then you get what you call a pony drivers job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You got that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, pony driving. Then - there was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 after}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  that there was the landing boy, you see. And after that was the - the putter. That's taking empty tubs into the coal face you see and men would fill them and you bring a full one back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were you a putter before the war started, before you joined up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No. No, I was just a - I was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925  just}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  a landing boy then as we call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 So you reached hat stage before the war and then you went back after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well used to - eight hours. Used to be ten hours on the surface, on the screens, and eight hours down below.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, not Sundays. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Not Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Just five days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Five days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 It was five full days, you wouldn't have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Five full days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh no, there was no holidays with pay them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How much were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - I think when I was on the screens ten hour day I got about ten shilling a week roughly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How did that go up when you were a landing boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well - well it wouldn't be much more I think. Wouldn't have been much more. Might have been a couple of bob or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well it was long hours you know for to work for it but of course you must consider in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 price}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  of foodstuffs those days and today. You see. Rents and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Compare that ten shillings with your three shillings from delivering papers there's a big difference isn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you do with the money you earned, did you give it all to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, we tipped it all up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get something back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I think I used to get ninepence a week pocket money. 'Course that was a - that was a canny bit them days. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And your mother put it in with the general housekeeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh it all went in with the housekeeping, you know, keep the - keep the house going and - and bringing them up and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you spend your ninepence on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh just sweets and pictures, I used to like to go to t
he pictures and the theatre, I used to like to - me young days like that I used to like to go and see plays. Cost me only about fourpence or threepence. I used to go to pictures every Saturday afternoon for a penny and tuppence, see the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 matinees}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 . I'm very fond of pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you get on O.K. with your workmates in your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh yes, yes, we seemed to get on well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about the boss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, you - you very seldom saw the - the head boss. There's what they call the overmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Those days, well the deputies and the overman, oh they were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well we liked it to a certain extent. It was - wasn't very nice getting up in the early hours of the morning to go to t
he pit like. 'Cos they used to be on the shift system you see. The three - four shifts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What did you do after that, you worked there until - what year did you enlist in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 About the ninth of the second '15. Aye. I was only about seventeen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 When did you go back to the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well, just before the war finished, about - perhaps about a fortnight before the before the war finished. 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You went back to what particular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Putting. Putting.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh well - I was only about two or three month then I re-enlisted again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You went back to the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Went back to the Army in - Royal Field Artillery this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did you stay in the Army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I was in - about two and a half year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You stayed in it after the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Aye. Was after the - the first war finished you see then I was back home a few month and I joined - enlisted again you see for six and six. But - I'd only served - about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 After you came out of the Army the second time what job did you do from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Oh well - 'course I was unemployed for a - a good while. I went - when I came out of the Army I had a job you see, to go to. That was down the pits again. In the colliery,
 South Hersey colliery. I had two year putting there, hand putting. No pony putting - hand putting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That's dragging the trucks along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes. Pushing them in and out you know to - to the coal face and bringing full ones out and taking empty ones in
 you see, -the tubs we call them tubs. They hold six hundredweight of coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That's up to about 1922 would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 19 - no, it wasn't all that time, there was - let's see now - I joined the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 
Artillery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  in about 1919 I think, somewhere about then and
 then I was two years over in Ireland. and came back. Then I got discharged on compassionate grounds. Then - I started at - at Elsey collieries - South }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 Else}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  and I was there twelve year. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 That's from about '21 to about '33?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Somewhere about '
30 or something like that or - '30's - 31 or 32 and they closed the seam down there. And of course I was paid off. You see, well I had a spell on the dole then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 About how long were you on the dole?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh - oh a good few months. Then I got a job on the buildings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Doing what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Hod carrying. A job I'd never done before nor - and - of course, those days a job was a job. And I was out - of a morning I went out practically every morning looking for work. Rather than be on the dole I went out o
f a morning just a cup of tea, perhaps a little bit of bread and butter, go out looking for work, round different places, building sites and that. Of course I got a job this morning then when I - when I was out one morning I got the job. I was hod carryin
g.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did manage to keep that going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
Well - was a bit awkward at first you know, going up this ladders with a hod on your - full of bricks you know. It was very heavy though, I used to work over ten twelve hour shifts. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 
'Cos you mixed your own lime and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4459925  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 cement up and that you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
You had all that to do, it was a tiring job going up the ladders all day you know. 'Cos as they - you - hod - hod full of bricks. There's some of the bricks weighs seven pound each. You get ten of them - eight and te
n of them in your hod you're going all day. It's a job. Still you get - you get used to it in the way like. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long did you keep that up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I was on it - about two years turned - two - about two years and three months or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Another spell on the dole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 How long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh, months again. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 And - there was a friend of mine, he got me - saw one of the bosses in the Vickers, he got me a job in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 What was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 'Course - it was a semi-skilled job. Testing castings with water pressure and so many pounds }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  square inch you know. And - it was heavy work sometimes, big castings you know you had to clamp them down on a table, big table with - nuts and bolts an
d one thing and another and big spanners and all that, and different sizes. But I was that job for - nearly twenty-five year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Until about 1960?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I was on that job practically twenty-five year then I had took a illness. And I was that was about -
 when I was about sixty, you see. Then - I was - had an operation, I was admitted to hospital and had a - an operation. Then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 I'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
 nine weeks in hospital came out, I was only out twelve days and I took a sort of a rupture again, I was back into hospital again. And I never got back to work anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 You'd be getting on for retirement anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 I was - I - I was on the six five years. 'Til sixty-five then I - but - retirement you see. Got me pension then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 If you could have chosen to do a different kind of job, would you have chosen other things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well jobs that I could have done might be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 If you'd had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 complete}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  choice what would you have chosen to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well really - I used to like down the factory like but - it was all - you 
know, oil and water and one thing and another on our job you see. But - you were out in the - in the - fresh air like, still when you're down the pits well - you're away from everything then you see. You're in the dark, there's just little davey lamp you 
see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Do you do any kind of training for any of jobs, any apprenticeships or any training periods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 
No, no, no, just - just carried on just as you got the job, well you were shown how to go on a little bit like but you - the chaps that you were with or anything like that you see. The chaps that was on the job well you learnt you see as you went on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you belong to any trade unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Well I did 'cos you - you - you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8602082\charrsid4459925 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925  had to be in a union like, well it was the Transport and General Workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you join that when you were in the mines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Oh that was - perhaps - fortnight when I went to the factory - Vickers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Were you in any union when you were in the mines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Yes, yes, I was in the Northumberland and Durham miners unio
n then you see. 'Course if you were off sick well you got so - you got so much sick money or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you take part in any trade union activities of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8918468 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 No, no, I didn't no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11365493 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13255302\charrsid4459925 Did you think that employers and workers had the same interests or were they different?
